Solid pseudopapillary tumor of the pancreas in a child: imaging findings with diffusion-weighted MR imaging. Solid pseudopapillary tumor of the pancreas is a rare tumor more common in young girls and rare in males.We present a case of a solid pseudopapillary tumor of the pancreas in a 13-year-old boy, with typical imaging features.Our case report specifically illustrates the potential of diffusion-weighted imaging findings on solid pseudopapillary tumor in pediatric patients.